I've updated both chapters to address your feedback. Summary of changes:

1. Fixed state-machine contradiction: §4.1 now agrees with §1.2 — every submit goes claimed→submitted, and §4.3 is the sole path to completed/failed. No claimed→failed shortcut.

2. Worker 'MUST NOT mutate' (03 §1 step 3) now explicitly excepts the outputs the role is specified to produce, cross-referencing §2.2/§3.2/§4.2.

3. Claim/token lifetime: 02 §3.4 now says claim MUST be present when state ∈ {claimed, submitted}. task.schema.json if/else updated to match. 04 §4.2 now states resubmit checks against the claim token retained on the submitted task; terminal transitions (§4.3) clear claim atomically; reclamation (§5.2) already cleared it.

4. Plan idempotency: 03 §2.4 drops 'order = preference' (priority is the ordering signal). 04 §4.2 content-equivalence notes proposal_ids are compared as sets.

5. eval_error trial status: 03 §4.4 and 04 §4.3 now specify that the trial stays 'starting' during evaluator retry, but MUST transition to 'eval_error' (terminal) when retry policy is exhausted or the operator abandons. This makes the enum value reachable.

6. Proposal dispatched→completed: 04 §7 implement-submit now MUST transition the proposal to completed on task completion (atomic with the event), instead of MAY.

7. Reclaimed implement-task trials: 04 §5.4 rewritten as 'Reclamation effect on role outputs' — on implement reclaim, the orphaned starting trial MUST transition to 'error'; a re-claim produces a new trial. Plan/evaluate cases also spelled out.

8. Reclaim-from-submitted: 04 §5.1 tightened — automatic reclaim (expires_at, health policy) MUST NOT apply to submitted; only explicit operator action may.

9. Host-model leakage in §4.3 (evaluator 'workspace'): rephrased as 'side effects MUST NOT be observable through any protocol-owned store, ref, or artifact location except via declared outputs.'

10. 03 §3.1 and §4.1 no longer claim the experiment config 'identifies' the repository. Repository location/access framed as role-binding concerns deferred to §6.

Please re-review the updated chapters at spec/v0/03-roles.md and spec/v0/04-task-protocol.md, plus the changes to spec/v0/02-data-model.md §3.4 and spec/v0/schemas/task.schema.json.
